@startuml AIRobotDetection_MainFlow
title AI Robot Detection - Main Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam titleFontSize 16
skinparam titleFontStyle bold

|JobService|
start
:POST /api/classificationJobs/robotAIDetection;
note right
  Parameters:
  - batchExternalSize: Batch size for external push
  - batchInternalSize: Batch size for PA insertion
  
  Ex: batchExternalSize = 1000, batchInternalSize = 5000
end note

:ScanningAIRobotClassification(batchExternalSize, batchInternalSize);
:Validate batch sizes > 0;

if (Valid?) then (yes)
  :InsertAIRobotClassification();
else (no)
  :Log Error - Invalid Batch Size;
  stop
endif

|Service Layer|
:Start();
note right
  Initialize robotDetections list
end note

:GetRobotDetections(RobotDetection_LastID);
note right
  **Get AI-Detected Robots**:
  
  1. Read System Parameter:
     - Key: RobotDetection_LastID
     - Get last processed RobotDetectionID
  
  2. Query RobotDetection Table:
     - FROM RobotDetection
     - WHERE RobotDetectionID > @LastID
     - ORDER BY RobotDetectionID
     - LIMIT (batch size)
  
  **Source**: AI/ML Robot Detection System ⭐
  
  **Returns**: RobotAIEntity[]
  - RobotDetectionID (for pagination)
  - CustID
  - CategoryID (Robot category)
  - LastModifiedDate
  
  **AI Detection Criteria**:
  - Automated betting patterns
  - High-frequency betting
  - Consistent time intervals
  - Machine-like behavior
  - API-based betting
  - ML model prediction
end note

if (Has robot detections?) then (yes)
  :Chunk by batchInternalSize;
  note right
    Split into batches for processing
    Batch size: batchInternalSize
  end note

  repeat
    :Process robot chunk;
    
    :Transform to InsertProblemAccountEntity;
    note right
      **RobotAIEntity → InsertProblemAccountEntity**:
      
      For each AI robot:
      new InsertProblemAccountEntity(robotAIEntity)
      {
        CustID: robot.CustID,
        CategoryID: robot.CategoryID,
        CategoryGroupID: Robot Group,
        // ... robot-specific fields
      }
      
      **Robot Classification**:
      - Category: Robot
      - Automated detection
      - AI/ML verified
    end note

    :InsertProblemAccountPackage();
    note right
      **Insert Robot PA Classification**:
      - FunctionId: RobotUserJob
      - CCInputFlow: InsertPACategory
      - Insert into CTSCustomerClassification
      - Apply Robot PA rules
      - Returns: Inserted CustIDs
      
      **Inherited Method** from ProblemAccountServices
    end note

    :PushExternalPackageByCustId();
    note right
      **Push to MainDB** (External):
      - Input: Inserted CustIDs
      - Parameters: pushConfig
        * RoleGroup: Member
        * IsUpdateDangerToMainDB: true
        * IsSyncAFCData: false (no AFC sync for robots)
      - Makes robot classification visible
      - Batch push for efficiency
    end note

    if (Push failed?) then (yes)
      :Return false;
      stop
    endif

    :Thread.Sleep(RobotUsers_SleepTimes);
    note right
      **Throttling** ⭐:
      - Sleep between chunks
      - Prevents database overload
      - Prevents API overload
      - Smooth processing
      
      RobotUsers_SleepTimes: Configurable (e.g., 100ms)
    end note

  repeat while (More chunks?) is (yes)
  -> no;

  |System Parameters|
  :UpdateLastScannedId(RobotDetection_LastID);
  note right
    **Update System Parameter**:
    - Key: RobotDetection_LastID
    - Value: MAX(RobotDetectionID) from processed robots
    
    **Enables**:
    - Next run starts from last processed ID
    - Incremental pagination
    - No re-processing
    - Resumable processing
  end note

else (no)
  note right
    **No AI robot detections**:
    All robots processed
    or no new robots detected
  end note
endif

|JobService|
:Complete;
note right
  **Job Completion**:
  All AI-detected robots processed
  System parameter updated to latest ID
  Ready for next job run
end note

note right
  **Key Characteristics**:
  
  1. **AI/ML Detection Source** ⭐:
     - Automated robot detection
     - ML model predictions
     - Pattern-based detection
     - Continuous monitoring
  
  2. **ID-Based Pagination**:
     - Uses RobotDetectionID
     - Incremental processing
     - WHERE RobotDetectionID > @LastID
     - System parameter persisted
  
  3. **Simple Flow** (no loop):
     - Get robots (one-time)
     - Process all in batches
     - Update parameter
     - Complete
  
  4. **Batch Processing with Throttling**:
     - Chunk by internalSize
     - Sleep between chunks ⭐
     - Prevents overload
     - Smooth processing
  
  5. **External Push**:
     - Push to MainDB after each chunk
     - Makes robot classification visible
     - No AFC sync for robots
  
  6. **Inheritance**:
     - Extends ProblemAccountServices
     - Reuses InsertProblemAccountPackage method
     - Consistent robot PA insertion
  
  **AI Robot Detection**:
  - Source: AI/ML Detection System
  - Automated pattern recognition
  - High accuracy robot identification
  - Machine learning based
end note

stop

@enduml

